<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-17T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851.01/3342: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Acting American Representative to the French Committee of
                                    National Liberation</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-17T16:00:00-04:00">January 17, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>161. Please draft an appropriate acknowledgment to Committee’s note
                                of January 8 quoted in your 129, January 12, and state that its
                                contents have been brought to the attention of the competent
                                military authorities of the United States.</p>
                            <p>For your information the matter has been referred to Admiral
                                    Leahy<note n="10" xml:id="d581fn10">Adm. William D. Leahy, Chief
                                    of Staff to the Commander in Chief of the Army and Navy.</note>
                                for information of and consideration by Joint Chiefs of Staff.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>